<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 3:42PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Wednesday Afternoon Heat Indices Around 100 Degrees...
The combination of afternoon temperatures in the upper 80s to
lower 90s with high humidity will lead to peak heat indices in
the upper 90s to around 100 degrees Wednesday afternoon.
Stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of the sun, and check
on relatives and neighbors. Young children and pets should never
be left unattended in vehicles under any circumstances. If you
must be outdoors, take frequent breaks and drink plenty of fluids.</description>
